{
  "semantic_description": "Checks whether a nonnegative integer up to eight decimal digits is an Armstrong number by first counting its decimal digits, then summing each decimal digit raised to that count with nested loops, and finally returning whether the sum equals the original input. The function is pure, does not modify memory, and returns true for 0 because the digit-count branch sets digits to 1 and the accumulation loop leaves sum at 0.",
